  "prompt": "How do you get a job in FIPB (Foreign Investment Promotion Board), India.",
  "response": "To get a job in the Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB) in India, which is now part of the Department for Promotion of Industry and Internal Trade (DPIIT), you can follow these steps:\n\n1. Educational Qualifications:\n- A bachelor's or master's degree in economics, commerce, finance, business administration, or a related field\n- Post-graduate degrees in international business or economics are preferred\n- Knowledge of foreign investment policies and regulations is advantageous\n\n2. Skill Requirements:\n- Strong analytical skills\n- Understanding of foreign investment regulations\n- Good communication skills\n- Proficiency in English and preferably Hindi\n- Computer literacy\n- Knowledge of international trade and investment policies\n\n3. Career Path:\n- Apply for entry-level positions through:\n  - Government job portals\n  - DPIIT official website\n  - Public Service Commission recruitment\n  - Direct recruitment notifications\n\n4. Recruitment Process:\n- Written examination\n- Interview\n- Background verification\n- Potential additional screening\n\n5. Preferred Experience:\n- Work experience in:\n  - Government departments\n  - Financial institutions\n  - Investment consulting firms\n  - International trade organizations\n\n6. Additional Recommendations:\n- Stay updated on government policies\n- Network with professionals in the field\n- Consider competitive exams like UPSC",
